def.p:
ISOPUB (and MathML 1) defined an fj ligature; 
   Unicode does not have a specific character and the entity was dropped from MathML2.
   It is re-instated here for maximum compatibility with .

U+03C6 GREEK SMALL LETTER PHI 
	(the definition used in HTML4); 
	MathML2 used  U+03D5 GREEK PHI SYMBOL.

U+23E2 and U+23E7;
	MathML 2 used U+FFFD (REPLACEMENT CHARACTER) as these characters were added at Unicode 5.0
	specifically to support these entities.

 U+27C8 and
	U+27C9;
MathML2 used U+005C U+02282 and   U+2283 U+002F.
